    "narrative": "For LawDog today, the lineup is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts our highest efficiency rating at 77.45. Despite facing a lefty in Matthew Liberatore, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits from a favorable park environment and a prime #3 spot in the order, making him our must-start anchor. **Bryson Stott** (72.46) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (71.36) are our next most efficient assets. **Bryson Stott** sees a massive 19% boost due to the soft matchup against Javier Assad, while **Geraldo Perdomo** benefits from a 16% park-factor surge that outweighs the concerns of hitting out of the #3 hole against a right-handed arm. These players represent our best path toward maintaining our edge in the scarcest category, SB, while providing the stability required to climb the Roto standings.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card was the exclusion of **Yainer Diaz**, who missed our \"Strong\" start threshold with a score of 38.75. While **Yainer Diaz** offers upside, the combination of a tough matchup against George Kirby\u2014whose xERA of 3.39 severely caps our run-scoring potential\u2014and a bottom-of-the-order assignment forced him to the bench. We are prioritizing efficiency and volume today, and **Yainer Diaz** failed to clear the 40.0 floor we set to protect our game caps. Investors should also monitor the lineup status of **Will Smith**, **Masyn Winn**, and **Lawrence Butler**; while we have modeled them into the lineup, late-breaking news regarding their placement in the batting order could shift their scores significantly, especially for **Lawrence Butler**, whose value is heavily tied to that lead-off spot against a high-tier arm like Nathan Eovaldi.",
